&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Container&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Text&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About The Company&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bosa Properties Inc. (“BPI”) is an end-to-end real estate company offering human-centered solutions for property development and management. Based out of Vancouver, Canada, our team of in-house experts work across residential, commercial and master-planned projects, with a growing residential portfolio that includes more than 22,000 homes that are built or under development, and an income portfolio that includes 5.5 million square feet of retail, industrial, office and rental properties under management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an organization of high achievers and believe what is created in community is always better than what is created in isolation. We set high expectations and support you in achieving excellence. We are building a trusted community to collaborate, learn from each other and deliver results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;#LI-Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Director, IT Operations, the (Senior) Cloud Infrastructure Engineer builds and runs the cloud platforms Bosa depends on, keeping our people productive, our identities and data secure, and our systems resilient. You&#39;ll look for every chance to make that easier through infrastructure-as-code, automation, and AI-assisted engineering, and partner with the rest of the Technology group and business users to protect what we run today and help shape what we&#39;ll run next.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a traditional sysadmin role. Our technology team is moving closer to the business, working alongside users to understand how work actually gets done, then using cloud-native tooling and AI to solve real problems where they add the most value. That includes opportunities to design and build internal web applications and tools with the business, where a custom solution is the right fit. We&#39;re a small, curious team that experiments, shares what we learn, and is energized by how quickly this space is changing. We&#39;re looking for someone who is genuinely interested in that shift, and who wants their day to be a mix of the fundamentals: identity, security, productivity, and resilience, and the newer work of figuring out where AI and automation fit best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineering and administration of AWS as our primary cloud platform (VPC, ECS, Route 53, IAM, EC2, S3)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Infrastructure-as-code using Terraform / OpenTofu to provision and manage AWS and SaaS resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administration of Microsoft 365 (Exchange Online, SharePoint, Teams, OneDrive, Intune, Defender)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administration of Microsoft Entra ID, including Conditional Access Policies, MFA, Privileged Identity Management, and risky sign-in / risky user remediation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Endpoint and identity security: least-privilege access, Defender for Endpoint, Intune compliance, and certificate lifecycle management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DevOps practices using GitLab and Git; branching, code review via merge requests, and CI/CD pipelines for infrastructure, scripts, and configuration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Containerized workloads using Docker and AWS ECS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scripting and automation in PowerShell, Python, and Bash, leveraging AI-assisted coding tools (e.g., Claude Code) to accelerate delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Backup, recovery, and resilience operations using Commvault Cloud; ownership of RTO/RPO compliance and DR testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cybersecurity operations: detection tuning, incident response, and vulnerability management&lt;/li&gt;
